#=============================================================================
# Wall Switch Configuration File
#=============================================================================
#
# FORMAT:
#   SWITCH_ID # SWITCH_NAME optional description
#       button N: TARGET_NAME
#
# Where:
#   - SWITCH_ID: Hardware identifier (5-6 hex characters)
#   - SWITCH_NAME: Human-readable name (no spaces, used for logging)
#   - button N: Button number (0-5 typically)
#   - TARGET_NAME: Name of the sONOFF target device (must match sONOFF.list)
#
# NOTES:
#   - Lines starting with # are comments
#   - Button lines MUST be indented (spaces or tabs)
#   - Buttons without mappings can be omitted
#   - SWITCH_ID formats:
#       * RFXCOM: 5 hex characters (e.g., 4AA03)
#       * KINETIC: 6 hex characters (e.g., AB6EDE)
#
# EXAMPLE:
#   AB6EDE # MY-SWITCH description here
#       button 0: G1G2G3G4-corridoio-principale
#       button 1: P4-area-bagno
#
#=============================================================================

